.TH "wait_for_completion_io_timeout" 9 "wait_for_completion_io_timeout" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
wait_for_completion_io_timeout \- - waits for completion of a task (w/timeout)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" wait_for_completion_io_timeout
.BI "(struct completion *x "  ","
.BI "unsigned long timeout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "x" 12
holds the state of this particular completion
.IP "timeout" 12
timeout value in jiffies
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This waits for either a completion of a specific task to be signaled or for a
specified timeout to expire. The timeout is in jiffies. It is not
interruptible. The caller is accounted as waiting for IO (which traditionally
means blkio only).
.SH "RETURN"
0 if timed out, and positive (at least 1, or number of jiffies left
till timeout) if completed.
